if you don't use -*:
    $1,must -> url
    $2 -> music name

-h -> get help
-c -> update app config
-version -> get version

-l -> get video config list
      $video_config -> list this alurm
            $media_name -> list this media(fuzzy select)
-o -> $video_config -> open this alurm dir
            $media_name -> open this media(fuzzy select)

-a -> add or updata video config
      $2,must -> video config key
	-> opt
 	     -rm $video config key
             -mv $new video config key
	     -custom $exe file path 
	     -set $key in video config [$value for this key]

-d -> download video
      $2,must -> url
      $3 -> download path(dir or file(no have .$media_type))
-d@a -> force download audio
        equals to -d
-d@v -> force download video
        equals to -d

-u -> upload to music
      $2,must -> vidoe path
      $3 -> music name

-p -> use video config
      $2,must -> video config key
      args....
-f -> choose video format
      $2,must -> video format
      args....
-pf -> use video config and format
       $2,must -> video config key
       $3,must -> video format
       args....
       
-F -> select format list for video
      $2,must -> video url
      $3 -> $load_code // select format for this load_code
            ${load_code}- // select format list for this load_code with like select

notice:
if use -p -f -pf, it must before every option

video_config help:
name -> video name
        video_name_allowed -> date,title,custom 
        (',' can be replaced to any char, 
        every item must use '@' as head)
matching -> video loader name
matching_sub -> sub macthing
      -> matching_sub_allowed -> url
